This paper is primarily focused on personalized item recommendation, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also deals with trust networks and social relations, which are relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social Computing (cs.SOC) sub-categories. The use of public anonymous feedback and user contributions in social networks is related to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new model and algorithm for personalized recommendation, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
